For decades all we got was a giant bathtub in return for millions in taxpayer dollars.  But we changed this - we got FULL funding for the Comite Diversion Project.  This means better protection for our:  - Homes - Businesses - Families  - AND lower flood insurance   (1/2) https://t.co/JNwyrtqQdw

Since the 2016 Flood we have secured $3 BILLION in federal funding for flood protection projects in South Louisiana.   AND we secured an extra $1.2 BILLION for future flood problems.  We must make these investments to better protect our homes businesses and livelihoods. https://t.co/IpCG8zjF36

South Louisiana fuels the nation.   We’re home to 5 of the top 15 tonnage ports in the COUNTRY.  We have to keep Louisiana as a top GLOBAL competitor to advance our state. (1/2) https://t.co/NhA57pzc3f
More information on wins we've secured to strengthen South Louisiana can be found below. (4/4)  https://t.co/OndUkGhkUj

By increasing the capacity on our waterways this helps alleviate the traffic congestion on the road.   These investments are a win in more ways than one and build on top of the successes we've secured. (3/4)

The major investments include:  - $13.4 million awarded to the Port of South Louisiana to bolster the port's production capacity. - $85 million to deepen the Mississippi River by 50 feet - $3.1 million to increase barge capacity between Baton Rouge and New Orleans   (2/4)

Better ports and deeper access points lead to a stronger Louisiana.  We have:   - 5 of the top 15 US ports  - 6 of the class-one rail lines - Proximity to the Gulf of Mexico - Access to the MS River & other major waterways   (1/4) https://t.co/2rnVORNhTP
